TITLE: Registering Object for Validation Messages in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet shows how to register the view with the `Messaging` service to enable visual feedback for erroneous user input. This is usually done in the controller's `init` function, which is called upon view initialization.  The registered object allows for validation messages to be displayed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sap/openui5-docs/blob/main/docs/04_Essentials/property-binding-91f0652.md#_snippet_17

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// "Messaging" required from module "sap/ui/core/Messaging"
Messaging.registerObject(this.getView(), true);
```

