TITLE: Controller Lifecycle Hook - onInit (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to implement the `onInit` lifecycle hook in an OpenUI5 controller. The `onInit` function is called when the view is instantiated. It's commonly used for initialization tasks like setting up models or attaching event handlers.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sap/openui5-docs/blob/main/docs/04_Essentials/controller-121b8e6.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
sap.ui.define([
    "sap/ui/core/mvc/Controller"
], function(Controller) {
    "use strict";
    return Controller.extend("sap.hcm.Address", {
        onInit: function() {
            this.counter = 0;
        }
    });
});
```

