TITLE: Declaring Module Dependencies - Good Example
DESCRIPTION: This example shows the correct way to declare a dependency to a module (`sap.m.Input`) within `sap.ui.define`. This ensures that the module is loaded before the callback function is executed, preventing errors caused by accessing unloaded modules.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sap/openui5-docs/blob/main/docs/05_Developing_Apps/javascript-code-issues-030fcd1.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
sap.ui.define(['sap/m/Input'], function(Input) {

    var fnCreateContent = function() {
        // reference sap.m.Input via a dependency
        return new Input({
            color: ...,
        });
    };
});
```

