TITLE: Defining a Module with Dynamic Dependencies in OpenUI5
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to implement dynamic dependency loading using `sap.ui.require` within an OpenUI5 module.  A static dependency on `sap/m/Input` is declared.  Within the `onSavePress` function, the `sap/m/Dialog` module is loaded dynamically only when needed. The callback function of `sap.ui.require` is executed after 'sap/m/Dialog' and its dependencies are loaded, creating and opening a dialog.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sap/openui5-docs/blob/main/docs/04_Essentials/modules-and-dependencies-91f23a7.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
sap.ui.define(['sap/m/Input'], function(Input) {

        var MyControl = ...;

        MyControl.prototype.onSavePress = function () {
            // dynamically load a dialog once it is needed
            sap.ui.require(['sap/m/Dialog'], function(Dialog) {
                var oDialog = new Dialog(...);
                oDialog.open(...);
            });
        };

        return MyControl;
    });
```

