TITLE: Changing Binding Mode in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code demonstrates how to change the binding mode for a specific property binding. It creates two `Input` controls bound to the same data in a `JSONModel`. The first `Input` uses a one-way binding, while the second uses the default two-way binding, demonstrating the difference in data flow.
