TITLE: Relative Date Formatting with DateFormat (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates relative date formatting using `sap.ui.core.format.DateFormat.getDateInstance`. It shows how to format dates relative to the current date (e.g., "yesterday") and illustrates the effect of the `relativeRange` property.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sap/openui5-docs/blob/main/docs/04_Essentials/date-format-91f2eba.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var oDateFormat = sap.ui.core.format.DateFormat.getDateInstance({
    relative: true
});

var nMS = 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24; // milliseconds in a day
var oDate = UI5Date.getInstance(Date.now() - nMS);
oDateFormat.format(oDate); // returns "yesterday"

oDate = UI5Date.getInstance(Date.now() + 7 * nMS);
oDateFormat.format(oDate); // isn't returned in relative format because the default value of relativeRange is [6|-6,]
```

