TITLE: Initializing OData V2 Mock Server in OpenUI5 (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet initializes the OData V2 mock server using `sap.ui.core.util.MockServer`. It creates a mock server instance, simulates the backend service using metadata and mock data, and then starts the server. The server intercepts requests to the root URI and returns mocked responses. It depends on the `sap/ui/core/util/MockServer` and `sap/base/Log` modules.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sap/openui5-docs/blob/main/docs/03_Get-Started/step-2-creating-a-mock-server-to-simulate-data-50897de.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
sap.ui.define([
    "sap/ui/core/util/MockServer",
    "sap/base/Log"
], (MockServer, Log) => {
    "use strict";

    return {
        /**
         * Initializes the mock server.
         * You can configure the delay with the URL parameter "serverDelay".
         * The local mock data in this folder is returned instead of the real data for testing.
         * @public
         */
        init() {
            // create
            const oMockServer = new MockServer({rootUri: "/"});

            // simulate against the metadata and mock data
            oMockServer.simulate("../localService/metadata.xml", {
                sMockdataBaseUrl: "../localService/mockdata",
                bGenerateMissingMockData: true
            });

            // start
            oMockServer.start();

            Log.info("Running the app with mock data");
        }
    };
});
```

