TITLE: Static Binding Part Example 1 - XML
DESCRIPTION: This XML snippet demonstrates using a static binding part with a common formatter function to achieve different behavior.  An Icon's 'src' and 'tooltip' are bound using the 'formatStatus' formatter, where a static part ('icon' or 'tooltip') dictates the return value.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sap/openui5-docs/blob/main/docs/04_Essentials/composite-binding-a2fe8e7.md#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: xml
CODE:
```
<!-- formatStatus returns a text or an icon source computed from the first two parts depending on the third part -->
<core:Icon decorative="false"
    src="{
        parts: ['deliveryStatus', 'paymentStatus', {value: 'icon'}],
        formatter: 'formatter.formatStatus'
    }"
    tooltip="{
        parts: ['deliveryStatus', 'paymentStatus', {value: 'tooltip'}],
        formatter: 'formatter.formatStatus'
    }"/>
```

