TITLE: Defining a Simple Control with OpenUI5
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet defines a new OpenUI5 control named `my.Hello` that extends `sap.ui.core.Control`. It includes a `name` property of type string and a renderer that displays the text "Hello <name>". The control's renderer creates a span element and inserts the greeting text with automatic XSS protection.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sap/openui5-docs/blob/main/docs/07_Developing_Controls/creating-a-simple-control-91f02ec.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
// "Control" required from "sap/ui/core/Control"

Control.extend("my.Hello", {                  // call the new Control type "my.Hello" 
                                              // and let it inherit from sap.ui.core.Control
    metadata : {                              // the Control API
        properties : {
            "name" : "string"                 // setter and getter are created behind the scenes, 
                                              // including data binding and type validation
        }
    },

    renderer : {
        apiVersion: 2,                        // see 'Renderer Methods' for an explanation of this flag
        render: function(oRm, oControl) {     // the part creating the HTML
            oRm.openStart("span", oControl).openEnd();
            oRm.text("Hello " + oControl.getName()); // write the Control property 'name', with automatic XSS protection
            oRm.close("span");
        }
    }
});
```

