TITLE: Handling the deviceready event in PhoneGap
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows how to listen for the `deviceready` event in a PhoneGap application. The `appReady` function, which contains the code that performs AJAX requests (such as OData model initialization), is executed only after the `deviceready` event is fired, preventing UI freezes caused by AJAX requests being blocked during PhoneGap initialization.  The `document.addEventListener` is used to bind the `appReady` function to the `deviceready` event.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sap/openui5-docs/blob/main/docs/05_Developing_Apps/development-for-hybrid-web-containers-293eb94.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: html
CODE:
```
<script>
<!-- put the following code in the beginning of the application code -->
function appReady(){
    // your code with AJAX requests
}
<!-- bind to the deviceready event -->
document.addEventListener("deviceready", appReady, false);
</script>
```

