TITLE: Core.ready() Promise with sap.ui.require in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to use the `Core.ready()` promise to execute code after the OpenUI5 framework has been initialized. It requires the `sap/ui/core/Core` module and uses the `then()` method to execute a callback function after the framework is ready. This ensures that application code is executed at the correct time, after OpenUI5 is fully initialized.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sap/openui5-docs/blob/main/docs/04_Essentials/initialization-process-91f2c90.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
sap.ui.require(["sap/ui/core/Core"], function (Core) {
    Core.ready().then( () => {
        // application can be started
    });
});
```

