TITLE: Using lazyInstanceof for Type Checks in OpenUI5
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates the use of a `lazyInstanceof` helper function for performing `instanceof` checks on dynamically required modules in OpenUI5. This function checks if the module is loaded before performing the `instanceof` check, preventing errors if the module is not yet available. It uses `sap.ui.require` to attempt to retrieve the module and only performs the `instanceof` check if the module is a function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sap/openui5-docs/blob/main/docs/04_Essentials/loading-a-module-d12024e.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```

function lazyInstanceof(obj, module) {
    var FNClass = sap.ui.require(module);
    return typeof FNClass === 'function' ? obj instanceof FNClass : false;
}

if (lazyInstanceof(oControl, 'sap/ui/base/DataType')) {

}
```

