TITLE: Adding CSS class to custom control in OpenUI5
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to add the `sapThemeText` CSS class to a custom control during rendering. The `oRm.addClass("sapThemeText")` method is called within the `render` function to apply the theme's text color to the control. This allows the custom control's text color to automatically update when the theme is switched.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sap/openui5-docs/blob/main/docs/04_Essentials/css-classes-for-theme-parameters-ea08f53.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// the part creating the HTML:
render : function(oRm, oControl) { 
	oRm.openStart("div", oControl); 
    oRm.style("width", oControl.getSize());  
    oRm.style("height", oControl.getSize());
    oRm.class("mySquare");       
    oRm.class("sapThemeText");  // here the CSS class is added which makes the text color depend on the current theme
    oRm.openEnd();
    oRm.text(oControl.getText()); 
    oRm.close("div");
},
```

