TITLE: Creating a Private EventBus Instance - SAPUI5 JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to create a new, private EventBus instance using the `EventBus` constructor. This decouples the new instance from the global EventBus, allowing for isolated event handling and preventing unintended side effects in other parts of the application.  It supports subscribing to and publishing on channels.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sap/openui5-docs/blob/main/docs/04_Essentials/deprecated-core-api-798dd9a.md#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
const oMyOwnEventBus = new EventBus();
oMyEventBus.subscribe("my-channel-id", "my-event-id")
oMyEventBus.publish("my-channel-id", "my-event-id", { /* data */ })
```

