TITLE: Overriding Control Property Setter Method
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows how to override the automatically generated setter method for a control property in OpenUI5. It demonstrates how to use `setProperty` to validate and store the new value and returns `this` to enable method chaining.  It modifies the behavior of the `setShowLogoutButton` method.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sap/openui5-docs/blob/main/docs/07_Developing_Controls/defining-control-properties-ac56d92.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
MyControl.prototype.setShowLogoutButton = function(show) {
    this.setProperty("showLogoutButton", show); // this validates and stores the new value
    return this; // return "this" to allow method chaining
};
```

