TITLE: Using autoWait in a specific waitFor statement
DESCRIPTION: This code shows how to use `autoWait` in a standard OPA `waitFor` statement. The `success` function will only be called when the control is found, its state is valid, and the app is responsive. In this example, the code asserts that the control is not busy.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sap/openui5-docs/blob/main/docs/04_Essentials/using-the-autowait-parameter-fb487ef.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
// in an OPA test
oOpa.waitFor({
    id: "myControlID",
    success: function (oControl) {
        Opa5.assert.ok(!oControl.getBusy(), "My control was not busy");
    }
});
```

