TITLE: Faking Timers with Performance API Mocks - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates how to use Sinon.JS fake timers in conjunction with mocking the Performance API. The code sets up fake timers and mocks the `performance.getEntriesByType` and `performance.timeOrigin` properties, which might be used by the code under test. After executing the test logic, it cleans up the mocks, executes any pending timer callbacks using `this.clock.runAll()`, and restores the original timers.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sap/openui5-docs/blob/main/docs/04_Essentials/sinon-js-spies-stubs-mocks-faked-timers-and-xhr-457eaad.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
QUnit.test("Test with fake timers", assert() => {
    // Setup fake timer
    const timeOrigin = performance.timeOrigin;
    const clock = sinon.useFakeTimers();
    // Mock performance API in case it's used by the code under test
    performance.getEntriesByType = function() {
        return [];
    };
    performance.timeOrigin = timeOrigin;

    ...

    // Cleanup
    delete performance.getEntriesByType;
    delete performance.timeOrigin;
    // Execute all pending timer callbacks
    this.clock.runAll();
    this.clock.restore();
});
```

