TITLE: Overriding Lifecycle Methods in OpenUI5 with JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to properly override OpenUI5 lifecycle methods such as `onAfterRendering` and `exit` in a custom class. It emphasizes the importance of calling the superclass implementation to maintain compatibility with future OpenUI5 updates.  It also showcases how to invoke the super class's method using `apply` to ensure the correct context.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sap/openui5-docs/blob/main/docs/02_Read-Me-First/compatibility-rules-91f0873.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
MyClass.prototype.onAfterRendering = function() {
  SuperClass.prototype.onAfterRendering.apply(this, arguments);
  // ...
};

MyClass.prototype.exit = function() {
  // Cleanups of your subclass ...
  // Invoke the exit method of the superclass at the end:
  SuperClass.prototype.exit.apply(this, arguments);
};
```

