TITLE: Override getFocusInfo and applyFocusInfo in OpenUI5
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows how to override the getFocusInfo and applyFocusInfo methods in an OpenUI5 control to preserve and restore focus after rerendering. It stores the ID and index of the focused element in getFocusInfo and uses this information to restore focus in applyFocusInfo.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sap/openui5-docs/blob/main/docs/07_Developing_Controls/implementing-focus-handling-91f19f0.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
sap.ui.define([
    "sap/ui/core/Control"
], (Control) => {
    "use strict";

    return Control.extend("my.custom.SampleControl2", {
        // ...

        getFocusInfo() {
            return {
                id: this.getId(),
                idx: this.myFocusElementIndex
            };
        },

        applyFocusInfo(oFocusInfo) {
            const oDomRef = this.getDomRef();
            if (oDomRef) {
                this.myFocusElementIndex = oFocusInfo.idx;
                this.focus();
            }
        }
    });
});
```

