TITLE: Implementing exit() Method in OpenUI5 Control (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to implement the `exit()` method in an OpenUI5 control. It shows how to perform cleanup operations, such as detaching event handlers and then calls the superclass's `exit()` method to ensure that the control is properly destroyed and to avoid memory leaks. It checks for the existence of superclass's `exit` method before calling it.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sap/openui5-docs/blob/main/docs/07_Developing_Controls/exit-method-d4ac0ed.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
SomeControl.extend("my.OwnControl", {
       ...
       exit: function() {
             //... do any further cleanups of your subclass, e.g. detach events ...
             this.$().off("click", this.handleClick);

             if (SomeControl.prototype.exit) { // check whether superclass implements the method
                    SomeControl.prototype.exit.apply(this, arguments); // call the method with the original arguments
             }
       }
})
```

