TITLE: Extending sap.m.Input with custom rendering (HighlightInput)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet extends the sap.m.Input control to create a new control called HighlightInput. The renderInnerAttributes method of the InputRenderer is overwritten to add a yellow background color to the input field. This allows customizing the appearance of the input field.  No specific dependencies are needed beyond OpenUI5 libraries.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sap/openui5-docs/blob/main/docs/07_Developing_Controls/extending-input-rendering-bcee26a.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
sap.m.Input.extend("HighlightInput", {// call the new Control type "HighlightInput" 
                                      // and let it inherit from sap.m.Input

			renderer: {
				// note that no render() function is given here. The Input's render() function is used. 
				// But one function is overwritten:

				writeInnerAttributes : function(oRm, oInput) {
					sap.m.InputRenderer.writeInnerAttributes.apply(this, arguments); // the default method should be called
					                                                                 // this will make sure that all default input attributes will be there

					oRm.addStyle('background-color', '#ffff00');  // this change could also be done with plain CSS. 
					                                              // But you get the idea...
					  }
				  }
			  });
```

