TITLE: Disabling autoWait for a specific waitFor statement
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to disable `autoWait` for a specific `waitFor` statement when you need to explicitly check for a blocking condition, such as a control being busy.  The `autoWait` property is set to false, allowing explicit checks to be performed without automatic waiting.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sap/openui5-docs/blob/main/docs/04_Essentials/using-the-autowait-parameter-fb487ef.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
// and then in a special waitFor case which requires a control to be non-interactable
oOpa.waitFor({
    autoWait: false,
    id: "myControlID",
    success: function (oControl) {
        // now you can explicitly check for some blocking condition
        Opa5.assert.ok(oControl.getBusy(), "My control was busy");
    }
})
```

