TITLE: JavaScript Step Definition with Context
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code demonstrates how to use the `this` context to share data between step definitions within the same scenario. Variables set in one step definition are accessible in subsequent step definitions. Each new scenario starts with a new `this` object.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sap/openui5-docs/blob/main/docs/04_Essentials/additional-options-for-feature-files-a509db4.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
this.register(/^I have a (.*?) in front of me$/i, function(coffeeType) {
  this.coffeeType = coffeeType;
});

this.register(/^I drink the coffee$/i, function() {
  this.sleepinessBefore = user.getSleepiness();
  user.drink(this.coffeeType);
});

this.register(/^I feel less sleepy$/i, function() {
  Opa5.assert.ok(user.getSleepiness() < this.sleepinessBefore, "Verified...");
});
```

